    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-05T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-05T04:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/11–550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drumright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-05T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 5, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 5—8:05 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. ReEmbtel 332<note n="1" xml:id="d748fn1">Received at 1:20 p. m. on November
                        3, <ref target="#pg_1030">p. 1030</ref>.</note> on Chinese Communist
                    activity in North Korea. According Eighth Army Intelligence, only significant
                    development <pb facs="1065" n="1045" xml:id="pg_1045"/> emerging past two days
                    has been spotting of considerable southbound vehicular traffic at various Yalu
                    River crossings in northwest Korea. Inasmuch as Chinese originally entered North
                    Korea with only three days’ rations and 100 rounds ammunition each, it surmised
                    southward traffic largely of supply character. With UN forces in Eighth Army
                    area regrouping and generally on defensive, few prisoners have been taken past
                    two days and only one found to be of Chinese race. No hostile air activity
                    reported past two days which perhaps due bad weather.</p>
                <p>Reports from Tenth Corps area which delayed as much as 30 hours in receipt here
                    indicate US Marines in contact with Sino-Communist unit about 20 miles north
                    Hamhung.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Drumright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
